---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Course — LLMs for Social Science"
  description="LLMs for Social Science: five modules from embeddings to agentic workflows, built for early-career social scientists."
>

  <!-- ── Status strip ───────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <aside class="status-strip" aria-label="Page breadcrumb">
    <div class="status-strip-inner">
      <span>Course</span>
      <span class="sep"></span>
      <span>LLMs for Social Science</span>
      <a class="status-cta" href="/course/day-1/">Begin Module 1 <span class="arrow">→</span></a>
    </div>
  </aside>

  <!-- ── Manuscript hero with TOC rail ──────────────────────── -->
  <section class="hero-manuscript">
    <div class="hero-ms-inner">

      <aside class="hero-ms-rail">
        <span class="rail-label">Course</span>
        <ol class="rail-toc">
          <li>
            <a href="#modules">
              <span class="t-num">01</span>
              <span class="t-name">Modules</span>
            </a>
          </li>
          <li>
            <a href="#begin">
              <span class="t-num">02</span>
              <span class="t-name">Begin</span>
            </a>
          </li>
          <li>
            <a href="#dates">
              <span class="t-num">03</span>
              <span class="t-name">Dates</span>
            </a>
          </li>
        </ol>
        <div class="rail-foot">
          <span>5 modules</span>
          <span>Open access</span>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="hero-ms-content">
        <p class="eyebrow-v3">LLMs for Social Science</p>
        <h1 class="hero-title h-display" style="margin: 16px 0 24px;">
          From embeddings<br>to agents.
        </h1>
        <p class="lede-v3">
          Language models are reshaping how social scientists collect, annotate, and
          analyze text. This course builds the conceptual depth and hands-on skills
          to use them critically. Beginner Python required; everything else is taught
          from first principles.
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── § 01 Modules ───────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="section-v3 section-v3--marker" id="modules">
    <span class="section-number">§ 01 · Modules</span>
    <div class="shell">
      <div class="section-head-v3 reveal">
        <div>
          <div class="eyebrow-v3" style="margin-bottom:14px">Five weeks of material</div>
          <h2 class="h-section">What you will learn.</h2>
        </div>
        <p class="lede-v3">
          The course runs from mathematical foundations to autonomous research agents.
          Each module builds on the last; start at Module 1.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="days reveal-stagger">

        <a class="day" href="/course/day-1/" style="text-decoration:none;">
          <span class="d-tag">Module 1</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="d-title">Foundations</h3>
            <p class="d-body">
              From bag-of-words to embeddings and tokenization, then contextual representations,
              language modeling, the Transformer, scaling laws, and how this stack shows up in
              social science workflows. The conceptual spine for everything that follows.
            </p>
            <span class="btn-link-v3" style="margin-top:14px; display:inline-block;">
              Open module <span class="arrow">→</span>
            </span>
          </div>
        </a>

        <a class="day" href="/course/day-2/" style="text-decoration:none;">
          <span class="d-tag">Module 2</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="d-title">From Models to Tools</h3>
            <p class="d-body">
              Post-training alignment (SFT, RLHF, DPO), prompting from zero-shot to
              chain-of-thought, reasoning techniques, and how to evaluate models and
              choose one that fits your task.
            </p>
            <span class="btn-link-v3" style="margin-top:14px; display:inline-block;">
              Open module <span class="arrow">→</span>
            </span>
          </div>
        </a>

        <a class="day" href="/course/day-3/" style="text-decoration:none;">
          <span class="d-tag">Module 3</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="d-title">Deploying for Research</h3>
            <p class="d-body">
              Fine-tuning (including LoRA-style adaptation and encoder heads), moving from
              notebooks to APIs and self-hosted inference, and rigorous validation — so a
              classifier works as a measurement instrument you can defend in publication.
            </p>
            <span class="btn-link-v3" style="margin-top:14px; display:inline-block;">
              Open module <span class="arrow">→</span>
            </span>
          </div>
        </a>

        <a class="day" href="/course/day-4/" style="text-decoration:none;">
          <span class="d-tag">Module 4</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="d-title">Extraction, Summarization, and RAG</h3>
            <p class="d-body">
              Faithful extraction and summarization (hallucination, omission, and distortion),
              then retrieval-augmented generation: chunking, embeddings, retrieval, and grounded
              answers with provenance checks over your own corpora.
            </p>
            <span class="btn-link-v3" style="margin-top:14px; display:inline-block;">
              Open module <span class="arrow">→</span>
            </span>
          </div>
        </a>

        <a class="day" href="/course/day-5/" style="text-decoration:none;">
          <span class="d-tag">Module 5</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="d-title">Agentic Workflows</h3>
            <p class="d-body">
              Building autonomous research agents with tool use, ReAct patterns, and
              multi-step orchestration. The frontier of what language models can do for
              your research pipeline.
            </p>
            <span class="btn-link-v3" style="margin-top:14px; display:inline-block;">
              Open module <span class="arrow">→</span>
            </span>
          </div>
        </a>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── § 02 Begin ─────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="section-v3 section-v3--marker section-tinted-v3" id="begin">
    <span class="section-number">§ 02 · Begin</span>
    <div class="shell">
      <div class="section-head-v3 reveal">
        <div>
          <div class="eyebrow-v3" style="margin-bottom:14px">Getting started</div>
          <h2 class="h-section">Open access. No registration required.</h2>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div style="display:grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 20px;"
           class="reveal-stagger">

        <article class="fb">
          <span class="rule-soft"></span>
          <h3 class="h-sub" style="margin-bottom:10px">Prerequisites</h3>
          <p class="copy" style="margin:0 0 16px; font-size:14px;">
            Beginner-to-intermediate Python. A Google account for Colab.
            No prior deep learning or NLP experience required; the course builds from
            mathematical foundations.
          </p>
          <a class="btn-link-v3" href="https://github.com/antndlcrx/Intro-to-LLMs-DPIR/tree/main/preliminaries"
             target="_blank" rel="noopener">
            Preliminary notebooks <span class="arrow">→</span>
          </a>
        </article>

        <article class="fb">
          <span class="rule-soft"></span>
          <h3 class="h-sub" style="margin-bottom:10px">Materials</h3>
          <p class="copy" style="margin:0 0 16px; font-size:14px;">
            All exercises are open-source Jupyter notebooks. Clone the repository,
            open in Colab, and follow along at your own pace.
          </p>
          <a class="btn-link-v3" href="https://github.com/antndlcrx/Intro-to-LLMs-DPIR"
             target="_blank" rel="noopener">
            GitHub repository <span class="arrow">→</span>
          </a>
        </article>

        <article class="fb">
          <span class="rule-soft"></span>
          <h3 class="h-sub" style="margin-bottom:10px">Start here</h3>
          <p class="copy" style="margin:0 0 16px; font-size:14px;">
            Begin with Module 1: the mathematical and conceptual foundations that
            everything else builds on.
          </p>
          <a class="btn-primary" href="/course/day-1/">
            Begin Module 1 <span class="arrow">→</span>
          </a>
        </article>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── § 03 Taught at ────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="section-v3 section-v3--marker" id="dates"
           style="padding-bottom: clamp(56px, 7vw, 88px);">
    <span class="section-number">§ 03 · Taught at</span>
    <div class="shell">
      <div class="section-head-v3 reveal">
        <div>
          <div class="eyebrow-v3" style="margin-bottom:14px">Spring 2026</div>
          <h2 class="h-section">Three institutions across Europe.</h2>
        </div>
        <p class="lede-v3">
          The course was delivered in person at three institutions in spring 2026.
          All materials remain freely available online.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div style="display:grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 20px;"
           class="reveal-stagger">

        <article class="fb">
          <img src="/img/partners/dpir_spring_school.png" alt="DPIR Spring School"
               style="height:44px; width:auto; max-width:200px; object-fit:contain;
                      object-position:left center; margin-bottom:16px;" />
          <span class="rule-soft"></span>
          <h3 class="h-sub" style="margin-bottom:6px">Oxford</h3>
          <p class="copy" style="margin:0; font-size:14px;">
            23–27 March 2026<br>
            <span style="color:var(--text-muted);">5-day intensive · DPIR, University of Oxford</span>
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="fb">
          <img src="/img/partners/essca.png" alt="ESSCA"
               style="height:56px; width:auto; max-width:120px; object-fit:contain;
                      object-position:left center; margin-bottom:16px;" />
          <span class="rule-soft"></span>
          <h3 class="h-sub" style="margin-bottom:6px">ESSCA Paris</h3>
          <p class="copy" style="margin:0; font-size:14px;">
            7 April 2026<br>
            <span style="color:var(--text-muted);">1-day workshop</span>
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="fb">
          <img src="/img/partners/eui.png" alt="European University Institute"
               style="height:44px; width:auto; max-width:160px; object-fit:contain;
                      object-position:left center; margin-bottom:16px;" />
          <span class="rule-soft"></span>
          <h3 class="h-sub" style="margin-bottom:6px">EUI Florence</h3>
          <p class="copy" style="margin:0; font-size:14px;">
            20–21 April 2026<br>
            <span style="color:var(--text-muted);">2-day workshop · European University Institute</span>
          </p>
        </article>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Base>
